  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing with the side of a knife, remove the skin<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and roughly chop</p><p>Chop your <strong>basil stalks </strong>and your <strong>basil leaves</strong> roughly, keeping them separate</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>‘Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>basil stalks </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the dish with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>orzo</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>creamy single soy</strong> and 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, cover with a lid, then put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until the orzo is tender – this is your <strong>one pot spicy 'Nduja & pepper orzo</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 22-25 min or until the tomatoes are soft and slightly charred – these are your <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in a large bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper and add to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-pepper-roasted-tomato-orzo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, give the <strong>one pot spicy ‘Nduja & pepper orzo</strong> a good mix up, top with the <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong> and serve the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the orzo is looking a little dry</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped basil leaves</strong> and a<strong> lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
